# What is it?

DeskDex is an application to help people navigate an open workspace.  It provides an interactive map of available desks and rooms and can provide details about users&#39; whereabouts.

Designated application administrators are responsible for the initial data entry and any necessary maintenance.  They supply the application with necessary floor plans, station types, and equipment, then register stations and place them on the map.  Administrators are authenticated by logging into Azure Active Directory.

Standard users can search, view the map, and view station details.  No authentication is required as this app is intended to be deployed internally.  If external access is needed, authentication can be enabled to require authorization to access any part of the site.

The work device is responsible for checking users in so that the application can track the location of personnel.  A script on the device will periodically check in with basic information about the user (their domain ID) and a unique identifier for the station that the user is at (typically the physical address of a dock ethernet adapter) to the API.

# Technology Used

DeskDex&#39; middleware is built on ASP.NET Core 2.06.  It depends on Entity Framework Core 2.0.2 for its data context.  It uses Microsoft SQL Server to store its data.  Its frontend is built with Material Design Bootstrap 4.5.0, jQuery 3.2.1, Zoomooz 0.1.3 for map interaction, Jcrop for station positioning in the management portal, jscolor for color selection in the management portal, and a URL search polyfill for Edge/IE compatibility.
